&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancy for a Full Time&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Trust Doctor (ST4+ equivalent) in General Paediatrics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are invited to apply for the above post at Croydon Health Services NHS Trust to commence as soon as possible for six months - extendable to one year. We are looking for an ambitious candidate who will contribute to a friendly and collegiate environment. This post complies with the junior doctor’s hour’s regulations.&lt;br /&gt;Croydon University hospital is a large District General Hospital with links to the local teaching hospitals. The Paediatric Department has 14 Consultants; 17 middle grades and 16 SHO equivalents as well as a well-developed Children’s Hospital at Home Team service. &lt;br /&gt;The Department has an excellent reputation for teaching and training and there are good opportunities for the successful candidate to develop their own teaching skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Croydon University Hospital has a delivery rate of 4,000 a year and is a sub-regional Centre for Neonatal Intensive Care. The Unit has HFO as well as conventional ventilation and cooling.&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate should have MRCPCH (part 1) or equivalent with full GMC registration as well as a minimum of two years’ experience at SHO/SPR level in Paediatrics. Part 2 holders would be an advantage. Applicants must be able to display organisational skills for the further development of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further details/informal visits contact: Dr Sereesha Veleshala, Consultant Paediatrician or Dr Priya Ramaswamy, Consultant Paediatrician on 020 8401 3000 Ext 5993&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
